Privacy Policy for Puke

This Privacy Policy describes how Lone collects, uses, and discloses your information when you use our multipurpose Discord bot, Puke.

・Information We Collect

We collect two types of information through the Service:

Information you provide directly: This may include your Discord username and ID, any commands or queries you submit to the bot, and any data generated by the bot's functionality that you choose to share.
Information collected automatically: This may include technical information about your device, such as your IP address and operating system, as well as information about your use of the Service, such as the commands you use and the channels you interact with the bot in.
・How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect to:

Provide and maintain the Service.
Improve and personalize the Service.
Develop new features for the Service.
Communicate with you about the Service.
Comply with legal and regulatory requirements.

・Data Retention

We will retain your information for as long as it is necessary to provide the Service and fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy. We may also retain your information for longer periods as required by law or to comply with regulatory requirements.

・Data Sharing

We will not share your personal information with any third party without your consent, except in the following cases:
To comply with legal or regulatory requirements.
To protect the rights, property, or safety of ourselves or others.
To provide certain features of the Service that are offered by third-party partners. In these cases, we will only share the information that is necessary for the third-party partner to provide the service.

・Security

We take reasonable steps to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no internet transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the security of your information.

・Your Rights

You have certain rights regarding your information, including the right to:

Access your information.
Correct inaccurate information.
Request deletion of your information.
Object to the processing of your information.
To exercise these rights, please contact us at [Your Email Address].

・Children's Privacy

Our Service is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and you learn that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete that information.


We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on the Service. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

・Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us on discord.
